Liskov Substitution & Open-closed principle

there are 2 important design patterns that can guarantee that the liskov substitution principle is not violated:
1. strategy pattern
2. template pattern


design principles (SOLID)
it serves us guide to allow scalable and maintainable software architectures
standards used to organize and arrange the structural components of Software Engineering design

design patterns
are more about how to design your code, and the concrete implementation of the design principle

